The random variables \(X\) and \(Y\) are independent, with \(X \sim N(5, 16)\) and \(Y \sim N(6, 9)\). The probability \(P(X > Y)\) is equivalent to \(P(X - Y > 0)\). Define \(D = X - Y\), which follows a normal distribution with mean \(\mu_D = \mu_X - \mu_Y = 5 - 6 = -1\) and variance \(\sigma_D^2 = \sigma_X^2 + \sigma_Y^2 = 16 + 9 = 25\), so \(D \sim N(-1, 25)\). The standard deviation of \(D\) is \(\sqrt{25} = 5\).

To find \(P(D > 0)\), standardize \(D\):  
\[
P(D > 0) = P\left( \frac{D - (-1)}{5} > \frac{0 - (-1)}{5} \right) = P(Z > 0.2),
