so:
\[
P(|Z| < 2.581) = 2 \times 0.9951 - 1 = 0.9902.
\]
Rounding 0.9902 to three significant figures gives 0.990. This value is the approximate probability using the normal approximation without continuity correction, which is standard for such proportion problems.

