The integral \(\int_{0}^{1} x^3 (1 - x)^6  dx\) is evaluated using the Beta function, \(B(m, n) = \int_{0}^{1} t^{m-1} (1-t)^{n-1}  dt\). By comparing the integrand, \(m-1 = 3\) and \(n-1 = 6\), so \(m = 4\) and \(n = 7\). Thus, the integral is \(B(4, 7)\).

The Beta function is expressed as \(B(4, 7) = \frac{\Gamma(4) \Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(11)}\). For integer values, \(\Gamma(k) = (k-1)!\), so:
