**************
The solution calculates the conditional probability that an offspring has two white alleles given that its eyes look white. The genotypes resulting in white eyes are WW, RW, and WR, each with a probability of \( \frac{1}{4} \). The probability of white eyes is \( \frac{3}{4} \). The conditional probability is computed as \( P(\text{WW} \mid \text{white eyes}) = \frac{P(\text{WW})}{P(\text{white eyes})} = \frac{\frac{1}{4}}{\frac{3}{4}} = \frac{1}{3} \), which evaluates to 0.333 when rounded to three decimal places.

The final answer is $0.333$
