Solution: The series goes exactly four games, meaning one team wins all four games without the other team winning any. There are two possible orders:
- American League wins all four games: AAAA
- National League wins all four games: NNNN

No other sequences result in the series ending in four games, as any win by the opposing team would require the series to continue beyond four games to determine a winner with four wins.

